label: Study arm
definition: Participants in Arm A lived in communities that received malaria camps (MCs) for the first time in year one. Participants in Arm B lived in communities that underwent routine malaria control in year one and received MCs for the first time in year two. Participants in Arm C lived in communities where MCs had already been implemented prior to the study period
